 "modules": [
  {
   "title": "Module 1 · Angle Facts",
   "html": "<p><b>Straight line:</b> angles sum to $180°$. <b>Point:</b> angles sum to $360°$. <b>Triangle:</b> interior angles sum to $180°$. <b>Polygon:</b> sum of interior angles of an $n$-gon is $(n-2)\\times 180°$.</p><p><b>Parallel lines cut by a transversal:</b> corresponding angles are equal; alternate angles are equal; co-interior (same-side) angles sum to $180°$.</p>",
   "examples": [
    {
     "q": "Find the sum of interior angles of a hexagon.",
     "a": "$(6-2)\\times 180° = 720°$."
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Module 2 · Perimeter & Area Formulas",
   "html": "<ul><li>Triangle: area $=\\tfrac{1}{2}bh$.</li><li>Rectangle: area $= l\\cdot b$, perimeter $= 2(l+b)$.</li><li>Parallelogram: area $= bh$.</li><li>Trapezium: area $=\\tfrac{1}{2}(a+b)h$.</li><li>Circle: area $=\\pi r^2$, circumference $= 2\\pi r$.</li></ul>",
   "examples": [
    {
     "q": "Find the area of a triangle with base 10 cm and height 6 cm.",
     "a": "$\\tfrac{1}{2}\\times 10\\times 6 = 30\\ \\text{cm}^2$."
    },
    {
     "q": "Find the circumference of a circle of radius 7 cm. Take $\\pi=22/7$.",
     "a": "$C = 2\\times\\tfrac{22}{7}\\times 7 = 44\\ \\text{cm}$."
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "title": "Module 3 · Sectors and Segments",
   "html": "<p>For a sector of angle $\\theta$ (in degrees) in a circle of radius $r$:</p>$$\\text{Arc length}=\\dfrac{\\theta}{360°}\\cdot 2\\pi r,\\qquad \\text{Sector area}=\\dfrac{\\theta}{360°}\\cdot \\pi r^2$$<p><b>Segment area</b> = sector area − triangle area.</p>",
   "examples": [
    {
     "q": "Find the area of a sector of a circle of radius 14 cm subtending $90°$ at the centre. Take $\\pi=22/7$.",
     "a": "$\\tfrac{90}{360}\\times \\tfrac{22}{7}\\times 14^2 = \\tfrac{1}{4}\\times 616 = 154\\ \\text{cm}^2$."
    }
   ]
  }
 ],
